Grand Chorus of Students in Pyongyang Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The grand chorus of students in Pyongyang "Korea, I Will Glorify Thee" was held in front of the main building of Kim Il Sung University on Mar. 30.
 The performance began with prologue "Historic Mt. Ryongnam" and the famous song "Korea, I Will Glorify Thee." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The audience was deeply moved by the wind-instrument music and chorus "We Will Follow Up the March that Started from Mt. Paektu," and mixed group singing and chorus "Song of the Movement for Reading 10,000 Pages" dealing with the immortal feats   Kim Jong Il performed by helping the students grow up to be dependable intellectuals of the revolution for the rosy future of Kim Il Sung's Korea and leading them to study hard so as to demonstrate the might of the motherland with science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Quintet poem "Songun Brilliant Commander of Mt. Paektu," wind-instrument music and chorus "Our General Is the Great Brilliant Commander of Songun " and other numbers clearly proved that Kim Jong Il is, indeed, the illustrious commander born of Mt. Paektu as he instilled the spirit of giving importance to the army and the spirit of prizing arms into the students as early as when he was conducting revolutionary activities at Kim Il Sung University. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also presented was the famous song "Dear General, Where Are You" in which the performers helped the audience renew their firm determination to successfully accomplish generation after generation the revolutionary cause of Juche under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il holding high the red flag of the revolution associated with the whole life of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance ended with wind-instrument music and chorus "We Will Defend the Headquarters of Revolution at the Cost of Our Lives."

Functions Held Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- A lecture was given at the Lahore Branch of the Pakistan-Korea Friendship Association on March 20 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 Mohammad Aslam Nagi, secretary general of the branch of the Pakistan-Korea Friendship Association, gave a lecture on the subject "Kim Il Sung, the everlasting august name". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the august name of President Kim Il Sung always shines with the Juche idea and the idea founded by him clearly indicates the way of national liberation, class liberation and human emancipation as it is the man-centered and people-centered theory, lucid philosophy of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Juche idea which all people adhere to is now dynamically advancing the human cause of independence for its truth and scientific accuracy. The august name of Kim Il Sung remains shining more brilliantly thanks to leader Kim Jong Il. It is thanks to him that Kim Il Sung is immortal and the President's idea and cause have been steadily carried forward generation after generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Round-table talks were held on March 22 on the subject "Immortal Flower Kimilsungia" under the sponsorship of the Kampala City Committee of the National Movement of Uganda. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants talked about how Kimilsungia came to go by the august name of the President and referred to the fact that a Kimilsungia festival is held in Pyongyang every year on the occasion of the Day of the Sun to draw various countries.

Rally on Situation Held in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The Reunification Solidarity reportedly sponsored a "rally on the situation to judge the corrupt conservative political forces in the April general election" at Myongdong Cathedral in Seoul on Mar. 27.
 Speeches were made and a resolution was read out there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resolution branded the intensive military maneuvers staged under various codenames despite the political situation created in the wake of the passage of the "motion on impeachment against the president" through the National Assembly as the U.S. undisguised interference in the internal and political affairs of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It expressed the determination to join the people in the struggle to shatter the second and third coup attempts of the political coup forces centered on the Grand National Party and the U.S. plot to intervene in the political affairs of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the rally, its participants marched along the street. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The security authorities deployed at least 300 riot policemen in the area around Myongdong Cathedral to crack down upon them.

Candlelight Actions against "Motion on Impeachment" in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- Candlelight rallies were reportedly held all at once in 35 regions of south Korea on March 27 in protest against the passage of "the motion on impeachment against the president" through the National Assembly.
 The People's Action for the Annulment of the 'Motion on Impeachment against the President' and Liquidation of Corrupt Politics (People's Action) sponsored a candlelight rally for the defence of democracy on the day of declaring the annulment of the motion and judging conservative corrupt politics in front of Kwanghwamun, Seoul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participating in the rally were at least 80,000 members of civil and social organizations, citizens from all walks of life, youth and students. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to the candlelight rally, the People's Action called a press conference to make public its action program for days ahead. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the press conference the organization clarified that it would conclude the candlelight rally at Kwanghwamun and open a citizens' square demanding the annulment of the "motion" and defending democracy near Myongdong Cathedral to start a full-scale campaign for collecting ten million signatures from April 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a signature campaign for the annulment of the "motion" was conducted by students around the venue of the rally under the National Student Council for Solidarity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At least 200 members of youth organizations including the Fellowship Society of the National Council of Student Representatives and the south Korean Council of Youth Organizations held a rally for winning a democratic reform in the spirit of the June resistance at Myongdong Cathedral. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A Pusanites' rally for the annulment of the "motion," the liquidation of corrupt politics and the defence of democracy took place in Pusan with at least 15,000 citizens attending as part of the candlelight campaign under the sponsorship of the People's Action.

Unreasonable Punishment against Chongryon Official Protested 
